<subSubSection id="C368650B322E9835FF1813D1FAEEFBD6" pageId="37" pageNumber="94" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8BCD3680322E9835FF1813D1FAEEFBD6" blockId="37.[151,1437,402,2011]" pageId="37" pageNumber="94">
<emphasis id="B906EA92322E9835FF1813D1FEFDFD36" bold="true" box="[199,321,726,751]" pageId="37" pageNumber="94">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
A 
<taxonomicName id="4C724D03322E9835FEB313D1FE4CFD37" authorityName="Suffrian" authorityYear="1866" box="[364,496,726,750]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Metallactus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="37" pageNumber="94" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B906EA92322E9835FEB313D1FE4CFD37" box="[364,496,726,750]" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="94">Metallactus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
of medium size, characterized by a fairly reduced black dorsal pattern. At first glance, this species looks very similar to 
<taxonomicName id="4C724D03322E9835FDA013FCFCABFCCA" authorityName="Suffrian" authorityYear="1866" box="[639,791,763,787]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Metallactus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="37" pageNumber="94" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="languidus">
<emphasis id="B906EA92322E9835FDA013FCFCABFCCA" box="[639,791,763,787]" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="94">M. languidus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but it can be distinguished by the stronger and closer pronotal and elytral punctation and the lack of impressions on sides of pronotum. Pronotal shape is also very distinctive in having lateral margin distinctly larger than in all the other species of the group, with the exception of 
<taxonomicName id="4C724D03322E9835FF481260FEAAFCA7" authorityName="Suffrian" authorityYear="1866" box="[151,278,870,894]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Metallactus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="37" pageNumber="94" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="spilotus">
<emphasis id="B906EA92322E9835FF481260FEAAFCA7" box="[151,278,870,894]" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="94">M. spilotus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
which is easily distinguishable by the very different general shape and dorsal colour pattern. Light colored specimens of 
<taxonomicName id="4C724D03322E9835FE4A128CFD96FC7B" authorityName="Suffrian" authorityYear="1866" box="[405,554,907,930]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Metallactus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="37" pageNumber="94" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="corruptus">
<emphasis id="B906EA92322E9835FE4A128CFD96FC7B" box="[405,554,907,930]" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="94">M. corruptus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can have a quite similar look, but they are easily diagnosed by the broadly yellow ventral side. The species looks somehow similar to 
<taxonomicName id="4C724D03322E9835FCF312A8FBEAFC1E" authority="Suffrian, 1866" authorityName="Suffrian" authorityYear="1866" box="[812,1110,942,967]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Metallactus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="37" pageNumber="94" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="verrinus">
<emphasis id="B906EA92322E9835FCF312A8FC12FC1F" box="[812,942,943,966]" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="94">M. verrinus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFE34B71322E9835FC6A12A9FBEAFC1E" author="Suffrian, E." box="[949,1110,942,967]" pageId="37" pageNumber="94" pagination="1 - 483" refId="ref45438" refString="Suffrian, E. (1866) Zur Kenntniss der Sudamerikanischen Cryptocephalen. Linnaea Entomologica, 16, 1 - 483." type="journal article" year="1866">Suffrian, 1866</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
which has not been included in 
<taxonomicName id="4C724D03322E9835FF6812D4FE97FC32" authorityName="Perty" authorityYear="1832" box="[183,299,979,1003]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Metallactus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="37" pageNumber="94" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="kollari">
<emphasis id="B906EA92322E9835FF6812D4FE97FC32" box="[183,299,979,1003]" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="94">M. kollari</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group because of the very different aedeagal shape. The latter is also different in having a much weaker dorsal puncturation, the pronotum slightly vaulted with narrower margins, lighter ventral coloration.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C368650B322E9836FF18151DFC96FEC4" lastPageId="38" lastPageNumber="95" pageId="37" pageNumber="94" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BCD3680322E9835FF18151DFC7FFB8F" blockId="37.[151,1437,402,2011]" pageId="37" pageNumber="94">
<emphasis id="B906EA92322E9835FF18151DFE7EFBEA" bold="true" box="[199,450,1050,1075]" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="94">Description of female</emphasis>
(male unknown). Habitus in 
<figureCitation id="13492A05322E9835FCD0151DFCE1FBEA" box="[783,861,1050,1075]" captionStart="FIGURES 13–14" captionStartId="36.[151,264,1883,1906]" captionTargetBox="[224,1371,202,1844]" captionTargetId="figure@36.[181,1405,193,1862]" captionTargetPageId="36" captionText="FIGURES 13–14. M. rileyi (13), M. bellatrix (14). 13a–b: habitus; 13c–e: median lobe of aedeagus in ventral (c), dorsal (d) and lateral (e) view [1.0 mm]; 13f: sclerites II–III–IV of endophallus [0.6 mm]; 13g: sclerite I and dorsal spicule of endophallus [0.9 mm]; 13h: spermatheca [0.8 mm]; 13k–m: rectal apparatus in dorsal (k) and ventral (m) view [0.9 mm]; 13n: antenna [1.5 mm]. 14a–b: habitus; 14h: spermatheca [0.7 mm]; 14k–m: rectal apparatus in dorsal (k) and ventral (m) view [0.9 mm]. 13a–b: holotype; 14a–b: holotype. Square brackets: length of scale segment." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3066650/files/figure.png" pageId="37" pageNumber="94">Fig. 14</figureCitation>
a–b (HT). BL = 
